text.tspan: Higher labor productivity and price levels in richer and poorer countries,
Labor productivity is expressed as the ratio of total GDP output and total numbers of hours worked. The ratio of PPP conversion
factor (GDP) to market exchange rate is taken as proxy for price levels.
